cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper discusses in-network computing using programmable networking hardware, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on Complex Event Processing (CEP), which involves processing streams of events, and can be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), software engineering (cs.SE), and programming languages (cs.PL).
